            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.35b.9"/>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                        <hi rend="caps">MEMO</hi>
                            <lb/>
                    from the desk of....
                            <lb/>
                        Mildred <hi rend="caps">R.</hi> Bennett 
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>July 29, 1971</dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Your big day is coming up Sunday at Bancroft. Wish I might be there, but I can't this time.</p>
                
                <p>On June 21 I was operated on for cancer. Fortunately they got all the growth on the biopsy but the surgery was radical, nevertheless, and I am not yet up to normal activities. There is no longer anything to worry about though.</p> 
                
                <p>Stan Smith was down to see me last week. He looks good, but is much distressed because his oldest girl has experimented with drugs &amp; has turned hippie &#8212; seeing no value in life.</p> 
                
                <p>Stan has nine more hours to finish his master's. He may go ahead and finish. He doesn't have a school for next year yet. He hopes to teach close to Kearney so he can leave his house 
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">MILDRED R. BENNETT</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    329 North Cedar
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">RED CLOUD, NEBRASKA</hi> 68970
                </fw>
                
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                        <hi rend="caps">MEMO</hi>
                            <lb/>
                    from the desk of....
                            <lb/>
                        Mildred <hi rend="caps">R.</hi> Bennett
                </fw>
                
                    there.</p>
                
                <p>This morning the bulletin from Bancroft came. It was full of interesting information. It sounds as if things are progressing. How wonderful that all this goes on while you are here to enjoy it.</p>
                
                <p>Our son, Bill is taking his surgical residency and seems happy and very busy. If he completes the residency, he will need four years.</p>
                
                <p>We are all fine here. We have taken no vacation on account of my illness, but will take a little time later when I am more nearly back to normal.</p>
                
                <p>Doctor Bennett wanted me to tell you when I went to the hospital, but I didn't want to worry you.</p>     
                <closer>
                    <salute>Love from all of us,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Mildred</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">MILDRED R. BENNETT</hi>
